reviewText: These pants are made by Cabin Creek for Woman Within.  My one pair was completely worn out so when I found a new source for them, I actually bought FOUR pairs!  I was in jeans heaven, they fit perfectly and AT the waist.  I have no idea what "slightly above the waist" means.  These pants fit perfectly.  Unfortunately, after about 5 months of wear, I was having to hold them up with suspenders!  CC has changed the elastic they once used and are now using that flabby elastic you might find in PJs.  They kept falling down and I would lug them back over.  It became a daily struggle.  So I returned them.  Gratefully, I found a couple of pairs of the original Cabin Creek jeans in my size at Sway.com and I am happy again.

reviewText:
This hoodie is very fun, warm, and pretty.  I like that there's a chin strap so that you can take it off (push it back) and it will stay on you, separately from the pom-pom ends.  The material is soft, and it isn't shoddily made.  Unfortunately, the horn arrived bent from being mailed, and over a month later it hasn't worked itself straight.  It also fits too large, and flops over my forehead and eyes.  I imagine if I were to wear a wig with hair up, it would stay up better.  It did not fit as pictured, and I can only get it to stay on well if I tie the pom-pom parts pretty tight.  When I do that, it squares up instead of being nice and round as expected.

It is still a fun little hoodie, but I would not spend this amount of money again for a similar product without trying it on first.
summary: Fun, furry, but way too large

reviewText: I bought this dress for a military ball. I ordered a size 2 and it came just as that but I am a very small person with a small bust. I had to take it to get it altered in the chest and along the sides. It was just a little too much wiggle room for my liking, but that was just me and I'm sure it would fit perfect on any other girl. After I got it altered and my fianc laced it up for me it ended up being too tight and I couldn't breathe at all that night, lol. But that was our own fault, nothing to do with the manufacturer. Another issue I had with it was it being too short. The part where the dress ended and the tulle started was up way too high, whenever I sat down you could see up to my mid thigh. It was very uncomfortable and awkward but again it might just be because of my body figure. Overall I would say this dress is good but I wouldn't recommend for any small girls out there that wear a size AA or A bra cup and are fairly short. Also make sure you order this dress a month ahead of your event because it took a long time for me to get mine.

reviewText:
You ever have that moment where you really want to look like a mad scientist...? Well I do about twice a week.  When that moment grabs me I reach into massive collection of sunglasses and pull these out.
The lens are nice and clear and the frame is chunky plastic as only the Chinese seem to be able to make.  The hinges work like a charm and as there is no nose piece they will never ever break. They harken back to a time when men wore white lab coats and reanimated dead bodies.
The funky chunky look would almost coax you into the thought that they are bakelite.  You would be wrong but they could easily pass.
So if your inner mad scientist needs to come out pick up a pair... They are super cheep, but well constructed so they are bound to be durable... So you should be good for years of wear.

reviewText:
I am 5'3" and dress size 0 - 2 depending on the  brand. This dress looks just like pictured above, and shipping was fast. Two points to make here: 1) it is one size fits all but this dress is not snug around the armholes and the waist seam falls 1/2" too low for me (altering that issue with my sewing machine). I think this is for someone who is between 5'2" to 5'8", if you are shorter, the torso is too long and if you are taller, your butt will show.  And I think this dress is (even though its sizing is not marked) US dress size 4 to 6. Size 8-10 ladies still would pull it off but it might feel a bit too tight around the chest is busty.
2) The fabric is not as "gutsy" as original Blackmilk clothing. The knit is still shiny and stretchy, but it is slightly "thinner" thus cheaper feeling. But hey, it is soooooo much cheaper and Blackmilk doesn't make this print anymore... so no complains. The price makes everything better!!!

To make matters worse, the price for the same set of earrings has now increased from $619.99 to $707.14 -so I can't even repurchase a different pair for the same price! I'm extremely disappointed with Amazon and not sure what to do with only a week left to find my better half a gift she deserves! In my attached pictures, you can see the black speck in the earring on the bottom right. It was hard to get my phone to focus in on it up close to get a good picture. At first, I thought it might be just the post that goes through the ear that I was seeing, but it's not. From a side view I could see the black speck right in the middle of the diamond. Additionally, warm-natured folks should be aware that the two layers of fabric, while sheer, do not breathe AT ALL - so it gets quite sweaty fairly quick.

The fabric is not loose or flowing as depicted, but rather made of a rough material that catches on the slip underneath (which ALSO isn't depicted, based on this product picture).  The fabric is also incredibly sheer, which necessitates the slip beneath, but it is unexplained and came as a surprise.

I ordered a medium based on the guide provided by the seller and expected a little slack in the shoulders.  It was far too tight -- I couldn't lift my arms without fearing that I would tear the seams in the armpits, and the sleeves barely covered the cap of my shoulder.  I couldn't move them down at all.

This is a cheap product.  If you're looking for something more appropriate for costume wear, I would suggest checking out an actual costume site.

reviewText:
I bought this for my boyfriend's 12yr old daughter for Christmas, who is obsessed with unicorns. Suffice to say, this was by far her favorite gift this year - score one for dad's awesome gf!

First, the material... as other reviewers have said, I was really impressed with the quality of the material. It is VERY thick and plush - definitely pj's for fall and winter months (in the summer only if you've got the AC running), and I could certainly see wearing this out for trick or treating as a costume and being totally warm and cozy inside. I cannot overstate just how good the quality of this material is. I really was expecting something thin, more like flannel pajama pant thickness (especially since I got it for such a low price - $24.99), but this measured almost a full inch thick, and is super soft!

Sizing. I know this is a hard thing to figure out when ordering online, so I wanted to include mine to hopefully help some people ordering in the future. This item is made to be worn baggy, so with the hood you really want to make sure you order one that will fit height. The girl this went to is 5'0 and 102lbs, thin build, and I ordered an adult Small. It fit great, and left her with a little room to grow. Her jean size is a girl's 12, and her shirt size is a girl's L.  I also tried on the unicorn before I wrapped it, just so I could add the extra info of how it fit me into my review... I'm 5'2 1/2, 125lbs, wear a size 6 jean, and have a 32FF chest - the small fit me great as well. As you can tell I've got a very "hourglass" shaped figure, but the fit was still very loose on me. I'd say anyone my height to to probably about 150lbs would likely be just fine with a Small. I think if you are over 5'3, though, then you should definitely look at purchasing the Medium, regardless of weight. Hope this is helpful!
summary: Great quality; size info in review

I like this writing pad quite a bit, but I have a few hesitations that stop me from giving it a 5. First of all, it has been several months since I've had this and it still has a bit of a strong leather odor. Normally, I would think that this odor would dissipate, but it is still hanging on. This could be a turn off in meetings if other people can smell it.

The second hesitation I have is that the rigidity of the pad comes from some cardboard on the inside, which makes this stiff and unyielding. It also means that if it gets bent out of shape there is no reversing it.

The last one is that the business card holder is not actually large enough to hold business cards. You would have to put them in at an angle, which sort of defeats the point.

Otherwise, this pad is large enough to hold a standard size laptop, a pad of paper, some business cards, and a pen. Good for travel.
summary: Not a bad choice for the price.

reviewText:
I fell in love with the color of these pants online and wasn't too sure what I'd be getting but thought it was worth the price to give them a try.

I'm SO glad I did! They're even more vivid and beautiful in person than in the picture and they're much better quality than I had even hoped for! They are thinner fabric so they'll be able to be worn in summer but not so thin that you feel exposed in them. At the moment I am a very curvy 165 pounds and I am 5'6" and these pants have enough stretch in them to be not only forgiving, but even very flattering to my Kardashain/Lopez sized behind. They look high waisted in the picture but on me they do sit a little lower because of my proportions. If you have less booty than I do though they will come up a little higher. They will fit a pretty wide range of sizes. I would say that if you are anywhere from 125 pounds to 175 pounds, these will probably fit you. I don't have much of a tummy but I can tell that if you do have a little bit it will still look flattering on. This fabric is NOT super tight. You can actually breathe and move in them. They are also a little longer so taller girls can wear them too.

I plan to wear these in Vegas with a long black tunic top that has mesh on the lower half of it and then some black ankle boots or sandals.

If you see these and love them, get them. They are fun and the jewel colors are gorgeous and they are totally worth it! As with any leggings, they should be washed in a mesh garment bag or by hand to keep them safe.
summary: Get these. You'll be happy that you did. :)

This top is comfortable & slimming. The fabric is soft & lightweight, but not see-through. It measures about 27 inches long from the highest point of the shoulder to bottom center. The neckline is a little low, but so are most of tops on the market. I use pins, some decorative, to fix this. My Bust is about 41 inches (38DD). The extra large fit perfect. My hips are almost 37 now. The sides on this top can be adjusted & tied tighter, which is flattering to those of us with smaller hips. Most tops that fit my bust, & not curve-clinging to my belly, are so big at the hips that they look like maternity tops. Not this one. It does not emphasize the belly area & yet does not look like a maternity top on me! Small miracle! The short sleeve top I bought of this brand fit the same. If my bust or hips were bigger, or if I liked tops over-sized, I would definitely go up a size. I am sure you could get this to shrink if it was a little big. I have not washed it yet.

I had ordered this wig twice before and I was sent the wrong color (both times, the first time it was bright red and the second time it was a brownish red) and there were some problems with it, however THIS TIME it was the exact color I needed.  I had found uses for the previous wigs which was a lucky coincidence.

Positives:
~exact color I needed
~the wig was pretty full for the price it was at, the netting only showed when I moved the hair around a lot.
~The netting for the wig was black, which is much less noticeable on this cover wig than if it had an off-white netting
~Wig fibers were soft and felt like real hair
~The curls were very well in tact
~It was packaged neatly
~Comes with a wig cap

Negatives:
~The shipping took a few weeks but I ordered this one during Halloween season so it was to be expected.

Advice:
~DO NOT use human hair products on synthetic wigs!  Some human hair products can burn through or damage the synthetic fibers! (especially hair sprays and shampoos)
~Condition the wig with synthetic hair conditioner (can be found at most local hair supply stores like Sally's) in order to avoid major frizz, which happens over time
~Do not keep the wig on the wig head for too long, if you aren't going to use the wig anytime soon it is best to pack it up and store it neatly in order to increase it's life expectancy
~DO NOT keep your wigs out in the open near fans, open windows, or anywhere prone to major gusts of wind, drafts, or heat
this can damage your wig.
~If possible, comb your wig gently layer by layer starting from the bottom. I usually use my fingers because It helps me have better control of how gently I comb, but if that is not your thing, use a wide tooth comb.
~I do not recommend using heat on this wig unless you want to straighten it. If you do use heat put it on the lowest heat setting.
~RESTORING CURLS
After a long time the curls will eventually fall out, but fear not, the best way to restore the curls is to gently rinse or dampen the wig, apply overnight curlers (no heat).  Since the wig would still be wet after you apply the curlers, gently lay it one half of the towel, then fold the other half of the towel over it gently and let it sit for 2 or 3 nights.  If you want the wig to be really curly, let it sit for even longer. The curls will come out pretty tight, but they will loosen a little bit when you let it sit on the wig head for an hour or two, then play around with it as needed.

reviewText: Coat looks and feels great.  I am 6,1" 290lbs.  No size issues at all.  Came in a tiny box that made think no way it's a good coat.  I was wrong.  I love it.

So I read a lot of reviews about this Pea Coat before I decided to purchase it, and I was extremely nervous going with the size I actually needed instead of a smaller, due to the large amount of review about the coat fitting somewhat large. I am a 3XL kind of guy, so a jacket being too large on a large guy is weird and unattractive... As far as I can tell, the jacket fit perfectly! it was loose enough to fit a hoodie underneath for the colder days, but tight enough where it gave me a full range of motion without swimming in my coat. I live in Wyoming, and our winters can be quite a bit nippy, but this jacket was perfect for me on the days where it lingered in the 30 degree range, and a hoodie underneath would leave me comfortable down into the teens. It is stylish, and the buttons are sewn on well. I also appreciated that it was a good length, I have had poorly made pea coats in the past that hadn't properly covered up my backside when I bent over, and... being a large man with issues of a revealing lower backside... this coat covered things up so I didn't feel so uncomfortable... My only complaint would be that one of my pockets already has a hole in it, but I do utilize my pockets, and it could have been I just put something too heavy in there, so that can chalk up to user error... not manufacturing flaws. I purchased the jacket back in November 2015 (It's now April 2016), and I have used it frequently and heavily. It's a great jacket, and if you are a larger man trying to look nice, this coat will do the trick. It doesn't hide the fact that you own a pet if you have one, though... But that is also something that is chalked up to user error.. dog hair + dark wool coat = hair galore... It's a great coat, and if you are seriously looking to buy one, I'd recommend giving this one a try
summary: A great coat for a good price!

reviewText:
These pants from Red Kap are very good. I am a contractor and I wear these everyday. I would normally wear out a pair of wranglers in a year. These pants are much more comfortable and breath alot better. These pants are super tough. I do alot of work in crawlspaces and attics and these have held up to everything I do.

The downsides is that they do fade. The pair on the left in the picture is after a year's worth of work. The pair on the right was just purchased. However I'm not in a beauty pageant so I don't care. Why I gave these four stars instead of five is that they do shrink a bit. They get a bit snug after washing them 52 times.

I would definitely order these again and plan on it. I will just order the next waist and length size up.

I love these pants. They fit well and look good but are still comfortable when bending and squatting. I have worn them twice in 100+ degree work environment, they are cool and don't hold sweat. They came out of the dryer wrinkle free, I just hung them up while they were warm out of the dryer and they looked great. I did have to burn a few loose threads but that's a one time minor detail. I know these pants are going to give me months of good service. My line of work is hard on clothes and 6 months on anything is a miracle.

No hesitation on giving these a 100% recommendation.

reviewText:
UPDATE:  7/27/18  -  I recently contacted the manufacturer of this watch and was told that it has been discontinued.

I have no idea why, since the HDE solar watch is an excellent value.  Amazon has sold out and Ebay has only
the yellow version of this watch left, and in limited supplies.  I purchased another one and two grey ones over
the past few months so that I have several of them for future use.

After several years I still say that this is the best value in watches on the market.  They keep great time,  have
several useful functions are only need a battery replacement every few years.  They are a tremendous value
and it's unfortunate that HDE has chosen to discontinue them.

UPDATE:  4/17/18 -  I just purchased two more HDE solar assist watches.  After several years of ownership and use,
I still highly recommend these watches. Given their reliability, practicality and affordable price, in this consumer's
opinion, there's nothing out there that can compete with them.

I've been using HDE solar power watches for several years now and I don't think that there's a better value in a watch to be found anywhere in the market place.  In reality the HDE is a solar assist powered watch, since it has a button cell battery that is constantly  recharged by the solar collectors on the HDE.  In my experience these batteries last about two years under constant use before they are no longer able to hold a charge.

You'll notice when they start to fail, because some of the watch functions will no longer operate properly.

Fortunately, the batteries can be purchased in volume packets so that the cost of each battery is around twenty cents, and watch kits which contain the tools needed to replace watch batteries can be had inexpensively.  If you consider how much you'd spend just to have a  jeweler change the battery in your watch, a watch kit can pay for itself in the one or two visits that you would make to a jeweler.

Moreover,  these  watches are more durable than one might imagine.  I've accidentally banged mine around on more than one occasion and they stand up well.

They also keep good time and have useful functions including:  both military and standard time,  the day of the week in both written as well as digital format, a stop watch, a programmable timer, and an internal light which can be activated with the push of a button, and which lasts for several seconds.  This is great if you like to walk or jog in the evening so that you can monitor how long you have been exercising.

The HDE is also water resistant.  That does not mean to go swimming with it. However, if you accidentally get the watch wet while you are washing your hands, you won't damage it.  I've seen this same watch for sale on other Websites for as much as $30,  so for less than $10 delivered,  the HDE  is a great value.

After several years of use I still highly recommend the HDE, since it's a terrific product for the money!
summary: Best Value In A Time Piece Available

I took it with me during military training in the field and get pretty beat up and it still works very well. I get compliments on it all the time and I am so surprised.

Unable to find more than one option locally (and that one verrry expensive for lower quality diamonds than this), I ordered three sandal pendants off Amazon for someone's "diamond birthday."  This was the second and more expensive sterling silver item.  (The other was  https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B007Z4KBXU/ref=oh_aui_detailpage_o04_s00?ie=UTF8&psc=1  for $39).  This is definitely higher quality than the other silver sandal and seems nicely made.  It's not as perfect as the official photo, but it's very good.  The prongs holding the diamonds are themselves rather large and shiny, so they tend to pop out more than the diamonds.  This may have been deliberate since even lesser quality, non-showy diamonds are expensive, and to have clear diamonds with laser-rainbows would be extremely expensive--but shiny diamond prongs are not so expensive.

The pendant came in a really nice box with ribbon.

The dimensions of the pendant are listed in the seller's description and I wasn't surprised by its size.  Amazon's "Product Dimensions" area in bold is notorious for being more the typical shipping box size, not the actual item's dimensions.

The gift recipient was offered the choice of this pendant and a yellow gold one, and chose the gold one.  (which was https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00159YAH4/ref=cm_cr_ryp_prd_ttl_sol_1  ) so I returned this item.

reviewText: Wayyyy to small.

The material is deceiving However still a pretty Spring Jacket it's so lite...I figure being that it was coming from China I'd need a bigger size so I went up 2 sizes and it barely fits and the belt popped on my second wear

Having had prior experience with sizing issues on items shipping from China, I knew to be wary of the size chart.  I've found them to be on the order of 2 sizes off of American sizes, and ordered a XXL to compensate...I thought.  No dice.  The size chart is nowhere near accurate for this item.  I would have to agree with the other reviewers on this point, and yes, it arrived in a padded manila envelope.  I was expecting a bit more of a cotton blend as written in the description. There is no 'care' tag on the item, but I would guess that it is 100% (or very nearly) polyester.  Luckily, it's nearly Christmas, and I can gift it to one of my Size 0 daughters (the sizing is that off!). Otherwise, I definitely would ask for a full refund. It's so thin that I would be embarrassed to put it in any of the "One Warm Coat" bins.  Shortly after ordering this coat (for $28), I found a true cotton/wool-blend peacoat, brand new, in a discount store for $20.  Unless you just like the style (it is cute), I say don't bother with this item.

Buyer, beware, while this coat may tempt you with the price and its cute style, it is not even worth the price you're paying.

First off, the sizes of this item as listed are completely wrong. The XL would fit my 7-year-old cousin better than it would a 27-year-old me.

Also, this item is made of incredibly cheap polysatin, which might keep you warm in a blizzard by southern Florida standards, but isn't acceptable for a warmish fall day in New Jersey, let alone the freezing temperatures we are already experiencing here. You are better off wearing a cheap fleece blanket for warmth. The buttons are incredibly cheap plastic, and one actually fell out of the polybag the item came in as I removed the coat from the package.

Basically, what I'm saying is you're wasting your time with this one. Seriously. Back away. Quickly.
summary: If It Seems To Good To Be True, It Is

My husband and I got married in August and this is the ring I chose for him. He absolutely loves it and gets constand complements on it. Everyone wants to know what it's made of and where he got it. Of course, they're always shocked to learn I DIDN'T pay a couple of hundred dollars for it! Almost 4 months in and, so far, this ring still looks as good as it did the day I got it. I would highly recommend this to anyone looking for a good quality, inexpensive ring.

My husband had asked me if I would mind him wearing a "replacement" wedding band while at work. He was concerned about his ring getting damaged or causing him to get shocked while working offshore on rigs. He had been wearing it around his neck on a chain and did not want to lose it, but wanted to be able to have that reminder of home when he was away. Of course, I didn't mind, so we searched online together to find a reasonably priced stand in that he did not have to worry about becoming easily damaged, conducting electricity, or costing a fortune to replace if it were lost or damaged. We came across this ring and purchased it when it was on an Amazon lightning sale. It is now a year later and he still loves this ring. He has taken to keeping his original wedding band, which had gotten a little snug, in a safe place and wearing this one all the time. The comfort grip style edging makes it more comfortable to wear than many other designs. I would highly recommend getting this ring.

I love this necklace set. Perfect length, seems sturdy. Unlike most cheaper necklaces, there is a loop built into the shape of the pendant to attach to the small connector ring which holds it into the chain (look closely at the image). Never a chance of not being able to reattach it if for some reason I need a new chain.

The bronze one is perfect, smoothly welded/pressed, nicely aged, uniform color, chain matches the pendant perfectly.

The silver one, however.... it's uneven, almost lumpy looking, in spots along the triangle (cloak) - not sure how that happened. Parts of the metal at the corners weren't knocked out properly. I fixed that myself with my pocketknife, not a big deal. While on the bronze pendant, the circle (stone) was attached minimally at both sides to the triangle (below the surface of the pendant on both sides), on the silver necklace, it is completely unattached on one side, and overly attached to the point of being visible on the other side. Finally, in the middle of the triangle, the wand is slightly thin at one point; it is not the same on the bronze pendant nor is it accurate. Very odd, but not so glaringly bad as to return it; unless someone gets about two feet away from my chest, they won't notice.

Again, these are both beautiful, and I intend to keep them both, but it seems as if the silver one was made with a different process than the bronze one, and it didn't come out as well.

Overall, very happy. Perfect length, hangs right on my sternum, not in cleavage or on collarbones. Sturdy construction,
summary: Beautiful, but why is one better quality than the other?

I like this more athletic fit and they are made out of Nike Drifit material that has a little bit of stretch. They are perfect for volleyball, as the name would suggest, but with 4, full-size pockets they can be worn in just about any setting shorts are appropriate. I've worn them as a bathing suit, out running errands, to the gym, jogging, beach volleyball, and they are at home in all of these tasks. The solid gray color makes them very versatile and doesn't scream swim trunks like brighter colors or tropical patterns.

A couple of caveats. They are probably a little too informal for golf and they do not have a liner. I don't mind the latter fact, but to some this is a must for use as a bathing suit.

I love Fedoras, but, after wearing them for over tens years, I decided to buy a Porkpie hat. I'm very pleased with this hat. It's made of good quality materials. The material is medium weight, so it's not too stuffy on warm summer days and nights in Southern California. The brim is slightly flexible, but it's not flexible to the point where the look of the porkpie hat can be altered. You won't be to have this hat double as a Porkpie Hat and as a Baby Fedora. The black band adds a nice contrast to the blue color of the hat I purchased. I've tried on other brand hats where the wool felt and the band were the same color, but I didn't like that look. This is an excellent hat and people have had positive comments on it every time I've worn it. Several asked where I got and wanted all the particulars. If, you want a Porkpie Hat, you cannot go wrong buying this one. I wear a 7 and 5/8, so the XL fits my head well without altering the shape of the hat. I hope you enjoy your Porkpie hat as much as I'm enjoying mine.

reviewText:
You will see wildly varying reviews of this dress, and I realized it all depends on what seller ships you this product from China.  If you are lucky like the ones who gave rave reviews, the dress will look just as photographed.  It will have a lot of extra, cascading fabric draping slightly longer on the sides than the middle.  It will be roomy, it will have the May&Maya tag and the straps will be adjustable.

If you are unlucky like me and have a dress shipped to you by ODIDI, you will be sorely disappointed (or livid) like all those giving 1 star only because 0 star is not an option.  What you will get is a very poorly constructed, thin, see through narrow boxy dress, with too long straps that are not adjustable, with tight chest area, and a shapeless narrow box of a body that does not have the extra fabric that causes the cascading and interesting hemline.  The adjustable strap is a critical feature to dresses like this, and even more so if the straps are already way too long.  The stitching will be very poor quality and the dress unfit for wearing out.  It will look more like a poorly constructed slip dress intended to be worn underneath something else.  Actually all my slip dresses are of infinitely higher quality than this piece of trash. The dress will arrive without any tags or labels other than one tiny size tag sewn on by an infant.  Although the listing describes the dress as being made of cotton, it is actually very thin, see through rayon that has zero drape and stretch.  A complete abomination all around.

If you alert seller ODIDI to the blatant bait and switch, expect no response.
summary: Be very careful who you buy from; stay away from seller ODIDI

reviewText:
Now if you need perfection. Walk away. The aiming/lasers are too big on the side of the helmet, and the black cover is not painted to go along with your color choice. I ordered the black silver, and my cover is black. The mesh eyes are barley glued in, and a some spots are bent into the plastic for a better hold. The top part of the bio mask is separate from the mask. So you have to insert the pegs into the holes, and slide them into place. Just be careful doing it as the plastic pegs want to give. In the middle brow above the eyes you see a perfect dot. Well that is a flat screw you have to put in once you've connected the top of the bio mask on. There are some gaps as it's not a perfect fit. If you're looking at this for a paintball or airsoft mask. It will just break on you. It is extremely unsafe, and I don't believe it was made for it. The straps are pretty lame as well. Same as the pegs. Just slide the hole over the peg, and slide it into the smaller position. Also another thing with my aim/laser I had to unscrew the back to uncover the lasers. Then I had to pry the circuit board out of its hole, and find a plastic pull sheet to get the batteries active. Just to find all three lights do not go on at once. There's four lights in total. The first light is a red laser, the second light is a really bright white led, the third light is a bright red led, and the fourth, and final light is a blue led. How is it all of the lights are different? Why is it I can't have three lights go on at once for a PREDATOR effect? I would send it back, but it being shipped to China I don't see me getting my money back. I might just repaint it, and keep it as a piece on my shelf.

I hope this review helps.

I just received this mask, which I bought as a gift for my 8 year old kid who is a fan of the Alien vs. Predator movie and wants to use it for paintball (hope it holds up!). My comments about the mask are mixed, there are good and not so good comments.  First, the good, the mask is beautiful and my kid really liked it. I read another buyer comment that he had to dismount the light to reach a paper tab which needs to be removed in order to get it working -- i'll try doing that tomorrow. Also, I wanted to comment that in the photos, the mask seemed to have a shiny surface, the actual mask (I bought the Silver) however is not shiny -- though, it does look good. This is an extremely well made and stylish jacket. However, please , even if you are a thin person, do NOT think a small will fit. I originally ordered a large after reading other reviews which stated to order at least a size larger. As I normally wear a small, a medium at most, I went ahead and ordered a "large" as I like to wear thick sweaters during winter and it would not zip past my chest. Admittedly, I wear a 36 D so that might be part of the reason as the rest of the coat was quite loose. Point is, I ended up having to order an extra large which is shown in photo. This coat is probably an American 8. Despite this weirdness with sizing, the jacket is very much well worth it, just be sure you order 1 or 2 sizes larger than you would normally. So if you normally wear a small, you should get get a large, unless you intend to not wear a sweater or thick shirt below it, for instance.  Otherwise this company is great! Great customer service, fast arrival, excellent clothing! The jacket even has double stitching! Seriously cool and well made clothing :-)

reviewText: If you can't take your wallet full of cards wherever you have to go, this is a good idea. I love it, and it comes in pink! :-)

I was looking for a wallet that looked a little more 'feminine' that did not require an entire other bag to hold it. Thankfully, I ordered this wallet, and it's exactly what I needed.

The wallet itself is small enough to fit in my hand, and can hold a large number of cards depending on the width of each card. I currently have about 7 cards in the cardside (the pink part), all of different widths. In the sliding tray, I hold all of my punchcards, loyalty cards and health insurance cards as well as a bill or two in the event that I need cash. the cardslide's mechanism works great and can be easily used with one hand. It's a great wallet for someone who doesn't want something large or bulky.

As for the color...I personally love this tone of pink. It's pretty subdued and not in-your-face at all. I'll admit that when I first got it, I couldn't stop staring at it--it's a very pretty pink. But if you're looking for a very bright pink that really stands out, you'd have to look for another wallet.

For years I've been carrying a bulky standard leather wallet. Stuff stuff and things in it and shove it in my pocket; weeks later I clean the wallet out and it is light again. This minimalist wallet from Holland is remains light because you can't stuff much in there. I have 6 cards in mine; two of them are embossed. I have the cardslide attachment which is great to have for some extra cards; I fit three in there and stuffed a few 20$ Bills there for when cash is king. If there are no cards in the cardslide attachment, it is a little difficult to stuff cash in there due to the design of the thingy in the bottom that holds items tightly.
I usually hold my leather wallet in my left hand and pull cards out with my right hand. It takes a little getting used to holding this Secrid wallet in my right hand and pulling cards out with my left hand. OR after I pull the lever, I put the wallet in my left hand and use my right hand to pull cards out (confusing, right?). I think if this wallet was left hand friendly, I'd prefer to pull the lever with it in my left hand.
Anyway, the RFID blocking is a bonus. This wallet doesn't really work in a back pocket, front pocket carry preferred or in cargo pants, or in a man bag :-P
If the lever sticks, take all the cards out and put them back in. Cards won't fall out unless you shake it super crazy hard or use rotational velocity to flick the cards out with your wrist.
Metal finish is nice and I love the blue color.
I'll be buried with this wallet unless a better version of this one is made!

There is something wonderfully special about the Cuddl Duds Softwear with Stretch products!  The fabric is incredible.  I use Cuddl Duds all year long (and I live in the hot south - New Orleans)!  I use the sleeveless ones under sweaters in the winter and alone as a tank in the summer and spring; sometimes I layer one color with another.  I use the round neck under a v-tee, the long-sleeved one in the winter, layered or alone. There isn't a day that I don't reach for a Cuddl Duds in one way or another.  I understand they are coming out with a tee this spring and I'll be sure to add those to my collection.  For me, personally, it's ONLY the "Softwear with Stretch" collection that I care for.  These shirts are well made and have lasted years through repeated washings!  A fantastic buy!
summary: I wear a Cuddl Duds every day, all year round!

reviewText:
I love this! This is a favorite comfort outfit. It is so comfortable!  It's cute but not too cutsy. The cotton fabric is kind to my skin. The cuffs at the wrists and ankles help keep me warm. The zipper makes it easy to get on and off. The hood is nice. It will keep your head warm when your hair is wet, like when you just get out of the shower. If you are wet in a cold room, this outfit is the fastest way to get something warm on. Don't stand there and shiver, step into this and sip it up and you will feel better right away.

For me, the best part is having no waistband. I have certain difficulties in the abdominal area, which you don't need to know the details of, but let's just say at the end of the day it is nice to slip into something that doesn't apply any pressure to that area at all. It's great. I can stretch and breath in this garment, and I love how comfortable I feel when I wear it. Big thumbs up on this one.

reviewText: Item arrived very quickly from the seller WHITE APPAREL (within 3 days w/ free standard shipping). These are seriously amazing. I'm 5'4" and 115lbs, small waist but large hips. These are the ONLY pair of fleece lined leggings I have found that are not see through on me (like I said, wide hips), even when you bend over. They are incredibly comfy and warmer than any other pants I have (wore them in single digits). I know people are complaining about a "chemical smell" but I've never found a pair of fleece leggings that don't have an odd odor. I don't think it's that bad as long as you aren't very sensitive to smells and I don't really notice it after the first wear. reviewText:
Okay, let's talk about how amazing these tights are. I'll preface this by explaining my usual trouble in finding a good pair of black tights.
I'm 5'2", 130 lbs and I've always had thighs of steel. What can I say, I'm a meaty yet surprisingly petite gal.
Any lady that's ever tried to purchase leggings knows the all to common problem of... the dreaded camel toe. Rest assured that these tights will not give you that! The fabric is so thick and stretchy that it smooths out any lump, jiggle or imperfection.
Another frequent problem is the opacity of the fabrics. Nothing is worse than finding a light, comfortable and flexible legging only to find out everyone can see the goods in daylight. Somehow these tights have managed to be lightweight AND completely opaque. Like I said, I'm in love.
The final selling point for me is the higher waist. I frequently fall victim to the pseudo muffin top created by pants that are too low on my hips, or lack there of. These come up just right before the belly button, and have a two inch thick band at the top to hold it all in place. As with the high-waist trend, I frequently get a cute pair of high waist pants, and the first time I sit down I feel like my abdomen is being crushed and I can't breathe. These tights won't do that! They stretch and move with your every movement. Seriously, I never want to take these off. ESPECIALLY given that the price is so low. Buying ten more pairs asap.
summary: let's talk about how amazing these tights are

reviewText:
I had quite the fiasco with another seller trying to buy a coat - different fabric, size, and color than the stock pictures. For this coat, therefore, I contacted the seller to get pictures of the actual coat instead of stock pictures.  The seller was courteous and sent me the pictures promptly.

The coat is beautiful, fits exactly as described, and looks great.  The color pink is slightly more rose-pink than the pictures make it look, and has a very soft shine to it.  The fabric is a nice fabric, and the coat is well made, including lining.

A steal at $40.  I plan to wear it while teaching as well as in more casual settings, which is exactly what i hoped for.  It came almost 2 weeks before the earliest estimated date, which was also nice (this shipped from China, and for me took 2 week from order date to having it in my hand).

Note also Chinese sizes are different than US sizes, so paying attention to the measurements they provide is key.  I bought according to measurements, and the coat fits exactly as it should.

It's a solid, sturdy-feeling umbrella with a comfortable grip. It won't blow away under heavy wind. However, the open/close feature is pretty bad. If you have the umbrella extended to the full length but closed, the open feature will not work. You have to manually shorten the umbrella, just to have it open fully. It will not work any other way, even if you try to manually open the top part of the umbrella without the button. Incredibly inconvenient feature.

I was detained at Vienna airport security yesterday for almost an hour due to my Brolly umbrella. I saw a creative handle design. Security saw brass knuckles. No - I am not kidding. I was not allowed to move. I was not allowed to sit. I was not allowed to consolidate my belongings to prepare for boarding. I was not allowed to be with my family. I was able to see my flight board. Apparently the police are not in the airport. I waited and waited. It was a frightening experience. Who knows how police think. BTW I am elderly and was on business for a major international corporation - i.e. not the profile of a scary person. Eventually the umbrella was returned and I got on my flight just in time. The umbrella went into a garbage bin in Heathrow.
summary: BEWARE Brolly umbrella looks like brass knuckles to airport security!!!

I got one of these for a March trip to Alaska a few years back.  I went to see the Northern Lights, and spent a couple of days/nights north of the Arctic Circle, and another few in and around Fairbanks.  Temperatures got down to the -15 to -20 degrees F, and I was good to stay out quite a while.  My recollection is that eventually my feet or face got cold, or I'd get sweaty and then chill a bit, but these coveralls did their job well.  Since I live in Baltimore, I've had almost no opportunity to wear this since that trip.  Maybe I'll spend a winter night stargazing and see if they're not too warm...Or maybe I'll wear this when I do my Antarctica trip.
summary: Pretty much as advertised - great cold weather gear.

I usually wear a size medium top in most brands, but I heeded the warnings in the other reviews and opted for a large. It turned out to be a wise decision. The material is of decent quality, the cut is gorgeous, and the shelf bra provides adequate support...for me. I have a smaller bust and a relatively narrow torso, and I found the top to fit my dimensions quite well. I wore to the gym a couple times already, and put it through pretty rigorous HIIT-style workouts that incorporated lots of jumping and floorwork, and the girls stayed put. However, I don't think it have been the case if I were even a cup size bigger. My only rub with the garment is the inadequate lining of the shelf bra. The bra itself is sturdy enough to strap you in, put if you have...ahem... reactive nipples, well everyone will know. However, it's easily fixed by slipping in those little inserts that most sports bras come with nowadays.
summary: Sexy workout top that holds up to high impact workouts, but nipple city if you don't wear liners with it.

reviewText: Picture is totally different from the actual product. Size is the way smaller.

I ordered the Meily Women's Winter Warm Lapel Trench.  I was aware that this would take quite sometime to ship and unsure if it would be good quality.  The price was a definitive draw, and I decided to take a chance.  I ordered on November 17 and received the item on December 15.  Upon opening it, the first thing I noticed was the quality of the material.  The photo online makes the coat appear fluffy and plush, but this material was quite thin.  I also quickly noticed that several of the buttons were loose and that small threads were visible from some of the seams.  I tried the coat on, thinking that it looked much smaller than the photo.  The coat in the picture comes down several inches below the models hips, and I could visually see that this coat was much smaller.  I did fit the coat, though it was a bit snug and only came to about belt level on my pants.  I am normally a small-medium, in shirts and wear a size 5/6 jeans.  I ordered a medium from this seller and was not pleased with the fit. This is not a coat I would wear to keep me warm or on a regular basis, though it would look cute as a fitted jacket with the right pants.  I would have never ordered this item if I had seen a picture of what it really looked like. The photo used by this seller is not representative of the quality or size of this coat.  I know that I was taking a stab in the dark ordering a $20 coat from China, but I could have taken that $20 and going to Wal-Mart and bought an inexpensive puffy coat that will keep me warm, last longer than this coat, and still looks cute.  Actually, that is what I did after being disappointed with this item.
summary: Meily Women's Winter Coat NOT as pictured

reviewText:
I just got my watch as a gift and after following the directions several times, I found it synched to the correct time within a half hour.  It has a nice clear display, when I hold my wrist just right, however, I hope I can get the watchband replaced with twist-flex band so I can re-position it on my wrist to see it better.

The two things that bring the rating down by a point include the fact that it doesn't have a second hand and it displays the date military style -- August 10th displays as "10-8" and it doesn't display the year.  But it does display the day of the week, and that's nice. After a few days, the display changed so that the month showed first, so by August 12th, the display showed "8-12", which is the way I prefer.

I just realized that even if I replace the watchband with a silver band, there's still a border inside the watch that is pink, so there will always be pink on the face of the watch.  But, I think the convenience of a self-setting watch is worth that inconvenience.

Maybe some day they'll develop an atomic watch that is narrower, more like a woman's watch.

TL;DR: Slim, well-made wallet that can take abuse.  Holds only what you need and not much more.

This wallet is simple and, as such, has a slim form factor, which is what I prefer because I wear my wallet rather than carry about a purse.  If you use the side with the pouch to hold a lot of coins, it can get fat (and heavy).  The card access from the top is great for holding a few cards, but not much more than that, and there is no way to organize if you are trying to carry more cards.  I typically carry just one credit card and my ID in the center card access part.  The internal card holder (the one in the pouch) is difficult to use (especially if you have coins in the pouch) and I do not use this one very often.  This wallet is beautiful and well made.  It has held up to constant abuse (I am not nice to my utilitarian things) and even after all this time there is not one loose stitch or busted seam.  The wallet feels a little plastic-y, but that is fine by me.

If I have any complaint about this wallet, it would be that it is inadequate to hold receipts, which is unfortunate for me because I save my receipts religiously.  It means that instead of having a wallet of receipts to clear out once a week or so, I have to be sure to file receipts every day from my pockets, which is inconvenient, but worth it to have a slim wallet profile.
summary: Slim, Well-Made wallet that withstands abuse

reviewText: Great Bag for men. As expected
Great bag.

I bought this for my husband two years ago and writing review now. Let me say he LOVES this bag. He uses it everyday and tells everyone how comfortable and awesome it is. It's stylish while being good for everyday use. He puts his IPad, notebooks and pens in there. More than enough space. Not sure if fake or real leather but man it's lasted and still looks great! I'm buying one for my brother!

I won't lie - I'm not easy on bags. In fact, most don't last a year around me. The handles get caught in car doors, I overstuff them, and quite literally take them everywhere - usually with either my laptop, several notebooks, or both.
Well, it's been a year, and this bag is still in one piece. For the most part. The tab for one of the zippers has come off.
And that's IT.
No broken seams, no lining torn, no strap breaking, no zippers become warped, not even a loose thread!
My cats have even 'kneaded' the bag - both the outside and the lining, and I can't find the damage - it withstood their sharp little claws (my quilt on my bed can't even say that!)
I prefer spiral-bound notebooks, the wire binding can easily come loose and tear holes in the bag lining - there's not a single puncture that I could find.
I'm impressed.
I wanted something that looked halfway professional, with a strap that sits across the chest (harder for someone to grab it and run if it's settled that way). This was the only wallet-easy item that fit the bill. Whether it's leather or faux leather, I'm not sure (would prefer faux leather - I don't condone the killing of an animal just so I can have a bag), but it's sturdy! It fits three to four large notebooks, or a couple small notebooks and my (fairly small) laptop. And it literally goes EVERYWHERE with me, due to the nature of my work.
Additionally, my cats approve of it, too. One of them is sleeping on it as I type this - but this brings me to the only issue I have - it's VERY hard to get cat hair off the lining.
summary: Very nice - Still in one piece, and the cats approved, too!

reviewText: The blazer was no even close in size. I based it off the measurements that was given.

I was so excited, the dress I ordered arrived early and I couldn't wait to try it on. I was almost positive it would fit because it was a bodycon dress. This is the first bodycon dress I have ever tried. I figured if I ordered a XXL it would fit my bust but still be stretchy enough to fit snug in my waist and my hips. Once again I figured wrong  my boobs are busting out at the seams, just way too tight to even breath but the waist is 3 or 4 sizes too large. The hips are actually a nice (not too terribly loose) fit. The length was as pictured, hits just at the knee. I am 5' 6" tall and 150 lbs. When I use a tape measure to take my measurements they are 41-29-41.

Here is the measurement chart for the XXL size in centimeters, I added the inches equivalent.
Bust 106 centimeters is 41.73 inches
Waist 92 centimeters is 36.22 inches
Hips 112 centimeters is 44.09 inches

I am very sorry it does not fit, because I really love the look of this dress.

I am quite large at 300lbs and 5'4", so what better example can anyone think of to really give these a test-wear? Here's an honest review from an online-leery pants shopper!

I love comfortable pants and leggings. I was very excited to see a 4-pak of leggings for about $32 for the 3x size I needed. After judging the current reviews, I figured it would be worth a chance. I ordered the 2 black/2gray 4-pak without expecting perfection.

The items came fast (thanks Amazon Prime!); the coloring was as expected, and the value is great. I am wearing the gray ones now and they are not see-through. I'm glad of that because my underwear drawer is "not boring!" May update later to let you all know how the black ones turn out see-through-wise.

They feel very comfy and they fit great - the only issue I have is the waistband rise in the back. A long enough shirt to cover will still be just fine, but I wish the back can go a wee bit higher to cover up the small bit of undies that show; hence the reason for the 4 star rating. I suppose lots of larger ladies understand the issue of pants and things not going up high enough in the back. I can bend over and jump around and the pants will not roll off my stomach, so that's a great feature!

In short, for about $32 for 4 pairs, these would be excellent for comfortable wearing to everyday stuff and hanging out at home. I'd likely buy them again; let's just see how their durability is. Thank you for reading!

UPDATE: Wearing one of the black pairs now; very comfortable, but do seem a bit more see-through than the gray ones. Still not much to worry about if your shirt is long enough!

One thing I did notice was that the waist rise in the back is much better, which leads me to believe that no two pairs of the same size are alike, so beware of this. Try on all pairs you receive! Hope this helps!
summary: Everything is Great - Except the Waistband

This is a beautifully made quality boot with one major flaw.

It seemed the makers of these shoes put a lot of thought into these shoes not sure why they overlooked the fact that these boots are way too narrow for their targeted audience.

Babies have fat feet. Some have very chubby feet. For that reason most baby shoe manufacturers err on the side of making a wider shoe to fit most of those chubby feet.  This manufacturer essentially shrank an adult shoe and put in a soft sole.

My daughter is currently a size 6.5 and i bought these in a size 7. While the boots are a tad too long, they fit her almost like socks In every other way including the shaft.

From what my pedi advises baby feet need relative freedom to grow( she's an advocate of letting babies go barefoot as often as possible) so this shoe is breaking that rule. Because its leather and a soft one at that im hoping it will loosen up with wear... But by the time that happens she may be in another size.

These aren't issues that should be present in a baby/toddler shoe. Most parents won't be bothered to stretch a kids shoe and they shouldnt be.

Hopefully they revisit this as these are very cute well made shoes but its all for naught if they will prove uncomfortable or detrimental to the wearer.
Luckily i bought them very heavily discounted or they would have been a return for sure.

reviewText: Searching for a new winter coat mid-season is not ideal, but I am so glad my search ended with Amazon.  This coat has everything I wanted: knitted cuffs, a cozy, removable hood, and a longer length.  The style is very flattering and has a slimming effect with the set in waistband.  Since I often walk in cold weather, the "commuter" length is perfect for keeping me warm.  The ivory is a nice change from the usual dark colors down coats are offered in.  I would recommend this coat to anyone!!

Pros:
Very warm, love the THICK knit cuffs (a must-have for me)
Big, strong zipper doesn't seem like it will get stuck easily, and snaps to keep wind out of the zipper (although I'm too lazy to use them)
Faux fur hood lining is nice looking and very soft, it caresses your cheeks when the hood is snapped around your chin
Elasticized waist (not obvious in picture) gives you a nice shape under all that bulk
Soft, warm liner in good-sized pockets (although one of mine had a hole when it arrived)
Very long for full coverage with boots (I'm 5'9" and it hits just below my knee, almost meets my 15" high boot)
Described as machine washable, so should clean easily, but I have not tested
Very fast free shipping, ordered Sun. arrived Wed.

Cons:
Black was shinier than pictured when it arrived, not as matte as the picture, but not as shiny as an almost identical coat also from this seller.
The 1X did seem baggy on me everywhere except my 48" bust, which was loose enough for bulky sweaters, movement, etc.
Hole in my pocket upon arrival
Seller's return policy

Overall:
This was the only coat that met all of my requirements and still looked fancy enough for a 30-something.  I was disappointed that it wasn't as matte as the photo, and that it really was too big for me. There were no black ones left in XL, so I ordered the bone and will keep which ever feels better. Normally an XL is too snug for me to really move like I want, but I'm crossing my fingers and will update when it arrives.

It was a great deal at $99, but after the restocking and return shipping, it seems average.  I wouldn't have bothered if the coat didn't have everything I was looking for.
summary: Very nice coat, but runs big

Let me start by saying that these are amazing socks! When I saw these on Amazon they looked and sounded really good so I took a chance on them and I have to say they have gone way past my expectations. They are made of a light combed cotton blend material which I want in a summer / spring sock, and they look and feel really good on my feet plus the fit is perfect!! In the description it says they are sized for a men's 6-9 shoe size and that description is spot on. I'm a size 8 1/2 and the heel actually stays on my heel and doesn't ride up like those one size fits all you usually get in the stores. And, there's 14 pairs of them as the photo I posted almost shows, in the photo there is only 13 shown because the 14th is on my feet. Like I said these are a light weight sock and not meant for cold weather wear and  not for someone over a size 9 - 9 1/2 shoe although they might stretch out enough to fit a bigger size. These socks will be replacing the lighter crew socks in my sock draw and I'm sure I will get plenty of wear out of them. I did receive a discount on these in exchange for a honest and unbiased review but let me assure you that if it weren't for the fact that this offer came with 14 pairs I would definitely be buying more at the regular price!

So these are some flipping awesome socks.  I know socks!  I love socks!  I am picky when it comes to the socks I wear!  These are high quality, comfortable, and the perfect length for me.  The colors are bold and bright but not crazy looking.  I did receive a discount on these socks in exchange for my honest review but since then I have bought another set from this company at full price, lol!  I highly recommend these socks if you are looking for quality, comfort, and style.  Great socks!  I had to hide them from my teenager and thats why I bought a second set, lol!

Okay, so Ive had these socks for about a week but so far, they're pretty amazing. The fabric is of excellent quality and they are extremely breathable and light. They stretch perfectly and honestly fit my feet so that the heel lines up with the ACTUALY HEEL ON THE HUMAN BODY. Not only that the socks don't seem to have excess material and I get the feeling that this is truly a one-size-fits all type of sock. It literally does not feel like its too tight and it feels like its a very flexible sock. Additionally, it seems like one of those socks that if it got old, it wouldnt necessarily generate holes while the rest of the sock remains intact. It actually feels like one of those socks that may lose a few threads here and there but still maintain the same silky feeling as day one. I wouldnt recommend washing this in hot water but even after I washed a few of these socks, they remained silky and hardly lost any quality whatsoever. They are a very high quality pair of socks that I would recommend with flying colors. One last thing to keep in mind about these socks is that, the colors they provide are of the more vibrant quality as in the greens and oranges are not muted so it would definitely be difficult to wear these socks as part of a business professional outfit. However, if you wear brighter colors these socks are definitely for you.

I may update this review, but here are my first impressions.

I got the jacket on discount plus I applied for the Amazon credit card to get an additional discount. So the price was definitely right.

This is the second Wilson Jacket I've owned in my lifetime. The other was in my Youth and I was very happy with it.

Shipping was slower than I wanted due to the lack of Prime Shipping. But the real aggravation was the lack of tracking details. However it showed up soon enough and well packaged.

The jacket is lighter (lamb vs cow leather) than others I've considered. So it likely won't provide quite the same protection if you down down on a bike. However it's very modern in style and softer than say a traditional biker jacket. I'm a medium built guy and it fits perfect in the arms even when stretched out on the handlebars. It's not too tight around the body but enough that it won't flap around in the wind.

The jacket is very comfortable. I like the zips on the wrist for easy in and out. The two outer chest zip pockets are great for glasses, wallet, phone etc.  Two side hand pockets are nice too plus two more internal pockets. It's a shame the liner doesn't zip out for warmer summer rides but it should be ok. Looks perfect for spring and fall weather rides. It would have been nicer if the draw buttons on the waist had a second snap to draw it in as there really is only one position making the feature more style than function.

So far I am very happy with it.  I may edit once I have more time with it.
Fits as expected, no loose or crooked seams.  No complaints whatsoever.

This is a great, wonderful and excellent Jacket. Whenever I wear it, it feels like a royal robe. I honestly recommend to purchase this must-have Jacket. If there's one thing I cherish, its a great Jacket.

It appears to be a very nice wallet/passcase. The leather is good quality & it seems to be what my uncle has been looking for. I purchased it as a gift. I will let everyone know as soon as he carries it & it see if it holds up.

The Wilson wallet arrived when promised. The leather is soft, but durable. The credit card slots are wide enough, without having to struggle to get the cards out. I will buy another just like it when needed.
summary: I will buy another just like it when needed

reviewText: Great jacket. I get lots of compliments. Had a popped seam in the sleeve that I had to have fixed and had to have a new zipper sewn in. (By my husband.)  I'll have to echo the negative reviews.  And I can see that both the comments that the fit is too small and too big could be right.  I'm 6' about 200#.  Based on the sizing information I ordered a large.  Large was about the right size through the body; maybe a little tight.  But the arms were essentially non-functional.  You couldn't reach.  There were no gussets at the shoulders like you would have with most motorcycle jackets.  I'd be doing good if I could get something out of my pockets.  I was going to try to exchange it for the next larger size . . but there was no way to do that.  Because the order was not directly sold by Amazon but rather supplied by Wilson's Leather I could only get a refund.  BUT, because the reason was it didn't fit . . I had to pay the return shipping.  Basically it cost me the return shipping charges just to try on the coat.  Risky business.  If I had been able to exchange it for a larger size it may have given me some room to reach in the shoulders . . but then the body may have been too big.  It's a well made coat.  I liked the leather.  It has a lining that isn't removable.  A little heavy.  If the shoulders would have had gussets that allowed one to reach I would have kept the coat.  As far as I can tell none of the Wilson leather coats have shoulder gussets or another expansion device at the shoulders.
summary: Needs shoulder gussets; no room in the shoulders

reviewText: The cosplay is great, the only thing is the headband could of been made a little better. Also the cosplay came right in time.

After a LOT of searching and comparing, my son had settled on this particular listing and seller.
First of all, my son is about 6'3" and approx 315 lbs.  Some times we can't find clothes or shoes (size 14) that fit him in a regular department store.  I have tried to purchase clothing for him online and so far, even the largest sizes are still too small for him.  His broad shoulders usually make shirts and coats look like their squeezing him.  We end up having to make costumes for him if he needs one.

Shopping for THIS "costume" in a size that would fit him was a chore.  I'm thankful that this seller had size 3XL.  I was worried that it still wasn't going to fit correctly.  Even though some listings (including this one) show a size chart, we find that a lot of times the sizes still don't fit right.  For me, it was a big risk since it's more than I normally like to spend on a "costume".  Plus since it's coming from over seas, returning it probably wouldn't be too easy.

Our purchase arrived quicker than I had expected.  I'm really happy about that because I was expecting to have to alter it some how.
When my son got home from school, he immediately tried it on.  To my surprise, IT FIT!!  ALL the way around!!!

The fabric was heavy duty.  I was very surprised that it wasn't really thin and see through like those Halloween costumes you get at the department store.  This one is going to last a while and he already said he wanted to wear it to school.  The buttons are a nice touch.  Detailed and sewn on well.  We saw no extra threads hanging.  The quality of the stitches were well done.

I'm very please with this purchase and recommend this seller if you're looking for a good "costume" suit.
summary: So surprised & happy that this 3XL actually fit as needed!
